Two probability variance tables. The first has two rows, labeled "X"
and "P(X=x)." The data in column format (X: P(X=x)):
        0: .15;
        1: .30;
        2: .25;
        3: .20;
        4: .10;
        The second table also has two rows, labeled "Y" and "P(Y=y)." The data in column format
(Y: P(Y=y)):
        0: .05;
        1: .05;
        2: .10;
        3: .75;
        4: .05;

