A probability table with two rows, labeled "Y"
and "P(Y=y)." The data in column format (Y: P(Y=y)):
            0: .98;
            1,000,000: .02;
            In other words, P(Y = 0) = .98 and P(Y = 1,000,000) = .02

A probability table with two rows, labeled "Z"
and "P(Z=z)." The data in column format (Y: P(Z=z)):
            10,000: .5;
            20,000: .5;
            In other words, P(Z = 10,000) = .5 and P(Z = 20,000) = .5
